1
00:00:05,362 --> 00:00:06,146
Hello, everyone.

2
00:00:06,166 --> 00:00:08,074
Thank you all for coming out tonight.

3
00:00:14,468 --> 00:00:23,974
Right now, we're in the middle of feasibility study, so getting to know a new phase of the project and getting to know the site, the community, and really putting a plan in place for the rest of this feasibility study.

4
00:00:24,354 --> 00:00:27,456
Our next submission is coming up in the end of June.

5
00:00:27,696 --> 00:00:39,443
Very important during this phase, during the preferred schematics work phase, to get as much community feedback as we can on all these options, and that really, really starts here tonight in a very significant way.

6
00:00:41,823 --> 00:00:45,566
So everyone will be facilitating a conversation in some way, shape, or form.

7
00:00:45,606 --> 00:00:50,350
We have structural engineers, we have HVAC engineers, some folks are more familiar with different parts of the project.

8
00:00:52,412 --> 00:01:02,019
So we had several visioning meetings for us as educators, administrators, to walk in the shoes of students through the halls and through their classes.

9
00:01:02,079 --> 00:01:07,604
Some of the most impactful moments of this work that we did together in teams were from our students.

10
00:01:07,844 --> 00:01:15,746
Really the purpose of this evening is to get some hands-on activity with the larger parts and pieces to understand what those relationships are.

11
00:01:15,766 --> 00:01:18,447
Everyone should also have a voice and vision card.

12
00:01:18,487 --> 00:01:23,908
It's like a postcard-sized document that if you don't have currently, we do have some around.

13
00:01:24,128 --> 00:01:27,929
We also have a couple of non-English translations as well.

14
00:01:28,629 --> 00:01:30,490
We have a priorities pom-pom table.

15
00:01:31,330 --> 00:01:37,055
At that table, what we have is a series of glass jars with some of the major priorities that we've heard to date from the community.

16
00:01:37,355 --> 00:01:40,718
And everyone, I think, has access to like three pom-poms when you visit the table.

17
00:01:40,738 --> 00:01:45,583
You can start to just get a sense of where the community preference for the different priorities are.

18
00:01:45,603 --> 00:01:49,366
A total of nine of those tables themselves grouped into the three alternatives.

19
00:01:51,708 --> 00:01:53,510
We've done this with the building committee already.

20
00:01:53,650 --> 00:01:56,513
We did it with the full high school staff on Tuesday of this week.

21
00:01:56,893 --> 00:02:03,779
So we're trying to generate just heat maps of interest from the whole cross-section of the Medford community, just to understand where interests are, right?

22
00:02:03,960 --> 00:02:09,245
It's not more or less scientific than that, but it is valuable to us to hear your feedback in terms of the different options.

23
00:02:10,397 --> 00:02:12,358
We're looking to open the building in fall 2030.

24
00:02:12,458 --> 00:02:19,142
The exact date is somewhat going to depend on which one of those 29 different options or what version of that we end up with.

25
00:02:19,162 --> 00:02:21,204
Some of them are going to be able to be completed more quickly.

26
00:02:21,284 --> 00:02:23,545
Some of them are going to take longer in terms of duration.

27
00:02:23,865 --> 00:02:26,947
And then by June, we will go from grid five to one.

28
00:02:27,447 --> 00:02:31,310
So sort of two sets of decisions where we are narrowing in.

29
00:02:31,470 --> 00:02:36,413
The building committee meetings are open to everybody and you're all welcome to join us at those meetings.

